      "userJourney": "1) The student completes enrollment and receives an invitation to add their student credential to a supported wallet app.\r\n2) They open the university issuer portal or follow a deep link from the student information system.\r\n3) The wallet receives the verifiable credential after the student confirms issuance.\r\n4) At the library gate or exam desk, the student opens the wallet and presents the credential (QR for proximity, or remote flow on the service website).\r\n5) The relying party verifies the presentation, checks enrollment status, and grants access without storing unnecessary personal data.",
